<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0818 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author analyzes the limitation of tactical and strategic armamentsin France and in Europe. It was understood very early in France thatif weapons of mass destruction were ever used, they would have effectsof such a magnitude that, unlike conventional weapons, they could neverbe the tools for the pursuit of political goals by other means, as onefamous guiding principle has it. At least this is true as far as democraciesare concerned. In the relations between the weak and the strong and ifthere is enmity between two States of unequal power, nuclear weaponshave a military meaning and are feared if, and only if, they are putto the service of the supreme interests of the sole nation which controlsthem.</TEXT></DOC>